Today=E2=80=99s interview is with Rescale ( https://rescale.com/ ) co-found=
er and CEO Joris Poort ( https://twitter.com/jorispoort ). Rescale delivers=
 high performance computing (HPC) in the cloud; its customer base includes =
7 of the top 10 global automakers, 7 of the top 10 global aerospace compani=
es, 3 of the top 6 global life science companies, chip design and energy co=
mpanies, and more. Rescale has raised over $200 million and runs over $1 bi=
llion worth of HPC workloads annually.

That, though, raises the question: what is HPC, and why is it so important =
to these industries? We cover exactly that in this interview, starting with=
 Poort=E2=80=99s groundbreaking work at Boeing designing the wing for the 7=
87, and how that led to the creation of Rescale, which sells cloud computin=
g, but does not actually run cloud computing data centers. We explore where=
 Rescale fits in the computing stack, how it sells its services, and where =
AI fits both in terms of the overall data center market and in Rescale=E2=
=80=99s future. I learned a ton in this interview, both about HPC and Resca=
le and also about the public cloud companies and how HPC investments laid t=
he groundwork for today=E2=80=99s AI buildout.

