are today, there=E2=80=99s not really enough data, there=E2=80=99s not some=
thing like the Internet you could just download and train on that, all the =
science and physics data.

*But if anyone=E2=80=99s going to be able to collate and get the data, it=
=E2=80=99s someone like you, that=E2=80=99s sitting at this nexus.*

*JP:* Yeah. Our vision is really to work with customers to ultimately let t=
hem empower the engineers and scientists to use that data to do the best th=
ings that they can do with that.

If you think of where we sit in the ecosystem and in the stack, it=E2=80=99=
s pretty important if you look at where things are going, how important cus=
tomer=E2=80=99s data is for all these AI problems, you want to be sitting a=
s close to that as possible to help the customers be able to take advantage=
 of that and if you think of the stack, so you start with say, Nvidia GPUs =
and AMD and Intel CPUs, they have the cloud provider ecosystem. They have a=
 layer like Rescale, and then above us you have these application vendors. =
We=E2=80=99re the ones who are trusted to manage all that data, and so we=
=E2=80=99re sitting right there.

We also have a lot of integrations with the ecosystem, so we=E2=80=99re lar=
ge enough that in verticals where we=E2=80=99re more mature, we have compan=
ies sharing, within Rescale, data with each other already and so that puts =
yourself in a good position to ultimately help these companies and the engi=
neers and scientists with these bigger AI problems that are coming down the=
 line.

*Well, I=E2=80=99m glad that I did not dive too long the Boeing discussion =
of what=E2=80=99s going on, because Rescale is actually much more interesti=
ng. We went very long, but I thought it was absolutely fascinating. I feel =
I learned a lot today. I think this was really interesting.*

*JP:* Awesome. Well, thanks for giving us the opportunity to explain what w=
e=E2=80=99re doing, and yeah, I=E2=80=99d love to follow up more on the Boe=
ing as well. I think there=E2=80=99s a lot of takes there that are interest=
ing, and we=E2=80=99ll see how that all evolves.

*Joris, it was great to talk, this was a fascinating conversation. And yeah=
, I look forward to seeing where Rescale goes next.*

